body:
## Bug

The `SessionStart` hook never finds `SKILL.md` and silently serves the hardcoded fallback ruleset instead of the real, level-filtered skill content.

## Cause

`plugin.json` registers the hook at `src/hooks/caveman-activate.js`:

```json
"command": "node \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/src/hooks/caveman-activate.js\""
```

but `caveman-activate.js` resolves the skill file one level up only:

```js
skillContent = fs.readFileSync(
  path.join(__dirname, '..', 'skills', 'caveman', 'SKILL.md'), 'utf8'
);
```

With `__dirname = <plugin_root>/src/hooks`, that resolves to `<plugin_root>/src/skills/caveman/SKILL.md`, which does not exist. The real file is at `<plugin_root>/skills/caveman/SKILL.md` — two levels up. The `catch` swallows the ENOENT, so every session gets the fallback block and edits to SKILL.md never propagate (contradicting the comment "Reads SKILL.md at runtime so edits to the source of truth propagate automatically").

The comment on line 51 also documents the old layout (`__dirname = <plugin_root>/hooks/`), which no longer matches where the hook lives.

## Fix that worked for me

Try the plugin layout first, keep the one-level path for standalone installs:

```js
let skillContent = '';
for (const rel of [['..', '..'], ['..']]) {
  try {
    skillContent = fs.readFileSync(
      path.join(__dirname, ...rel, 'skills', 'caveman', 'SKILL.md'), 'utf8'
    );
    break;
  } catch (e) { /* try next location - hardcoded fallback below if none found */ }
}
```

Verified on Windows 11, Claude Code Desktop: before the patch the hook emitted the 1,215-char fallback; after, it emits the 3,076-char level-filtered SKILL.md body.

Same `__dirname`-depth issue likely applies to any other path in `src/hooks/` scripts that assumes the old `hooks/` location.
